main event: On 30 August 1956 in Omaha, Nebraska, a circular object the size of a pea with a bright yellow-white light was observed for twenty-one minutes, exhibiting erratic zigzag movements.
interesting points: The observed object was described as being the size of a pea with a bright yellow-white light.
It orbited erratically with zigzag movements from the horizon.
The observation lasted for twenty-one minutes, providing ample time for detailed examination.
The document lists several possible conclusions for the observed object, including being a satellite, balloon, aircraft, space vehicle, astronomical object, or unknown.
The report is classified as a UFOB (Unidentified Flying Object) report.
